data.title: Australian tennis star Sam Stosur and partner Liz Astling share baby joy on Instagram
data.meta_description: Australian tennis star Samantha Stosur’s partner Liz Astling has given birth to a baby girl.
data.text:
Australian tennis star Samantha Stosur’s partner Liz Astling has given birth to a baby girl.

The Australian tennis player shared a sweet family snap with bundle of joy Genevieve, writing that it has “been one of the most exciting and happy times of (her) life.”

“On the 16th of June, my partner Liz gave birth to our beautiful little girl, Genevieve,” Stosur wrote on Instagram.

“It has been a whirlwind but we could not imagine life without her now.

“Mum and Evie are doing well and its so amazing to be home with them both.

“We are absolutely in love with this little bundle and rolling with the happy chaos.

“We can’t wait for what’s to come and to watch little Evie grow up... although not too quickly we hope!”

It is the first child for the couple.

The 36-year-old new mum has not confirmed if she will return to the world stage when Tennis returns next month, with the New York tournament going ahead on August 31 despite Wimbledon being cancelled.

The Queenslander is a former world number one in doubles and a former world number four in singles.

Stosur collected almost US$20,000,000 in prize money.

The Aussie fan favourite is currently ranked 97th in the world as of March 2020, but won the 2011 US open, beating superstar Serena Williams.

The 36-year-old’s stunning victory made her the first Australian woman since former world number 1 player Evonne Goolagong to take home a grand slam singles title.
